FILE LIST:
==========
CMakeLists.txt		Cmake build file
dtgtest.cc		Test tool source
p4dtg-test.rc           Windows rc/version file
README			This file

Plugin Test Tool:
=================
The tool uses the command line to issue calls to load, use, 
and unload plugins. The 2-character commands are listed 
below along with any required arguments:

Library
        LL path                 - new DTGModule(path)
        LT                      - DTGmodule::test()
        LN                      - dt_get_name()
        LV                      - dt_get_module_version()
        LC server user pass     - dt_connect(server, user, pass) -> dtID
        LF                      - delete DTGModule()
        LE<cr>datestring        - extract_date( datestring )
                                - datestring: -as specified by the plugin-
        LI yyyy mm dd hh mm ss  - format_date( date )
        Q{uit}                  - Quit tool. Exit will also quit tool
        H{elp}                  - Show this help text

Attribute - Optional plugin interfaces
        AL                      - list_attrs()
        AV name value           - validate_attr( name, value )

        The following are only effective prior to the LC command.
        AS name value           - set attribute
        AD name                 - delete attribute

Server (these require dtID to be set before use)
        SF                      - dt_free(dtID) Unsets dtID
        SV                      - dt_get_server_version(dtID)
        SW                      - dt_get_server_warnings(dtID)
        SM                      - dt_get_message(dtID)
        SL                      - dt_list_projects(dtID)
        SU                      - dt_accept_utf8(dtID)
        SO                      - dt_server_offline(dtID)
        SD                      - dt_get_server_date(dtID)
                                  May require project connection
        SP project              - dt_get_project(dtID, project) -> projID

Project (these require projID to be set before use)
        PF                      - proj_free(projID) Unsets projID
        PS                      - proj_list_fields(projID)
        PL n d datef userf user - proj_list_changed_defects(projID, ...)
                n:      max rows to return
                d:      yyyy/mm/dd/hh/mm/ss modified since date
                datef:  ModifiedDate field name
                userf:  ModifiedBy field name
                user:   Exclude user
        PD defect               - proj_get_defect(projID, defect) -> defectID
        PN                      - proj_new_defect(projID) -> defectID
        PR f1 f2 f3             - proj_referenced_fields(projID)
	
	PI<cr>			- proj_segment_filters(projID, ...)
	Field1 Opt1 Opt2 ...	  Each field/options set is on its own line
	Field2 Opt1 Opt2 ...
	.			  Terminate with a solo period

	The following are specific to the Perforce plugin:
        PQ n qual - proj_find_defects(projID, ...)
                n:      max rows to return
                qual:   qualication to use on query
        PC defect               - proj_list_fixes(projID, defect)
        PA fix                  - proj_describe_fix(projID, fix)

Defect (these require defectID to be set before use)
        DF                      - defect_free(defectID) Unsets defectID
        DL                      - defect_get_fields(defectID)
        DW field value          - defect_set_field(defectID, field,value)
        DR field                - defect_get_field(defectID, field)
        DS                      - defect_save(defectID)
